    response: "🤝 **Consent, Boundaries & Healthy Relationships** 🤝\n\nHealthy relationships are built on mutual respect, trust, and clear communication. Understanding consent is the foundation of any intimate interaction.\n\n1. **What is Consent? (F.R.I.E.S.)**\n   - **Freely given**: It is not consent if it's pressured, manipulated, or under the influence of drugs/alcohol.\n   - **Reversible**: Anyone can change their mind at any time, even after they've already said yes or started the activity.\n   - **Informed**: You can only consent to what you know. (e.g., if you agree to sex with a condom, and the partner removes it without asking, that is a violation of consent called 'stealthing').\n   - **Enthusiastic**: It should be a clear \"Yes!\" not a \"maybe\" or \"I guess so.\"\n   - **Specific**: Saying yes to one thing (like kissing) doesn't mean saying yes to something else.\n\n2. **Red Flags in a Relationship:**\n   - Extreme jealousy or trying to isolate you from friends/family.\n   - Checking your phone constantly or demanding passwords.\n   - Pressuring you to send intimate photos or do sexual acts you aren't comfortable with.\n   - Gaslighting (making you doubt your own memories or feelings).\n\nIf you ever feel unsafe, pressured, or uncomfortable, **you have the right to leave and seek help.**"
