    response: "🤰 **Pregnancy, Options, and Care** 🤰\n\nIf you suspect you might be pregnant, the first step is to take a deep breath. You have time to figure this out, and there are professionals who can help you.\n\n1. **Taking a Pregnancy Test:**\n   - Home pregnancy tests are very accurate if taken **after** your missed period. If you take it too early, you might get a false negative. If your period is very late, take a test.\n\n2. **If the Test is Positive:**\n   You have options, and the decision is entirely yours. Depending on your local laws, your options generally include:\n   - **Parenting**: Choosing to give birth and raise the child. Prenatal care should begin immediately.\n   - **Adoption**: Choosing to give birth and legally placing the child with another family or individual.\n   - **Abortion**: Choosing to terminate the pregnancy. A **medical abortion** uses pills (mifepristone and misoprostol) and is safely done at home up to 10-11 weeks. A **surgical abortion** is an in-clinic procedure. Both are highly safe medical procedures when done legally and by professionals.\n\n3. **Miscarriage:**\n   - A spontaneous loss of a pregnancy, usually in the first 20 weeks. It is very common and is **never your fault**. If you experience heavy bleeding, severe cramps, and tissue passing, see a doctor immediately."
