    response: "🩺 **What to Expect: Your First Gynecologist Visit** 🩺\n\nGoing to the gynecologist (OB/GYN) for the first time can feel intimidating, but knowing what to expect makes it much easier! You usually have your first visit between ages 13 and 15 for a basic health chat, and your first pelvic exam/Pap smear at age 21 (unless you have painful problems earlier).\n\n**What Happens:**\n1. **The Chat**: The doctor will ask about your period (when it started, how heavy it is, cramps), if you are sexually active, and if you need birth control or STI testing.\n2. **The Breast Exam**: The doctor feels your breasts to check for unusual lumps. It takes about 30 seconds.\n3. **The Pelvic Exam (If needed)**:\n   - You lie back and place your feet in footrests (stirrups).\n   - The doctor looks at your external vulva.\n   - They gently insert a specialized tool called a **speculum** into the vagina. It feels like pressure but shouldn't hurt.\n   - **The Pap Smear**: Using a tiny soft brush, they swab the cervix to collect cells and test for HPV/cancer. It takes 5 seconds. You might feel a quick pinch or cramp.\n\n*You always have the right to ask the doctor to stop, to ask for a smaller speculum, or to have a parent/friend in the room with you!*"
